			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=293952">Eastern Wastes</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Tain Hammerfrost</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Tain Hammerfrost</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=364225"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:">Dimbly</a> | 
		                        2/14/2001 5:55:12 AM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">A couple days ago having just crossed the bridge into Eastern Wastes I noticed a Coldain mystic (Tain Hammerfronst) limping through the snow.  As I approached him he colapsed into a heap.  When I hailed him he told me how he had been ambushed by frost giants and that they were probably tracking him at the moment to come and finish him off.  He asked for my help.  When I told him I would help him he told me to get the elixir from their leader (I'm sorry I can't remember the name, it started with a G).  The elixir was the only thing that could save him.  I looked on tracking for this giant.  He was there, but before I could see in which direction he was I was being pummeled for double hits of 130 dmg.  I didn't even see em before I was watching snow fall into my eyes.  Had I been facing the proper direction I would have seen them coming.  As it was I had no chance to even attempt to run.  This named giant leader was blue on tracking.  I'm a level 44 druid.  Anyone else ever met Tain Hammerfrost?  No one in the zone had heard of him that day.
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
